        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 9:49AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 948 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Jacks Creek, or 9 miles east of Henderson, moving northeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thurman, Saltillo, Jacks Creek, Lick Skillet, Sardis, Milledgeville,
Montgomery, Reagan, Haney, Hinkle, Roby, Bath Springs, Five Forks,
Pleasant Grove, Cabo, Garrett, Red Walnut, Beacon, Enville, and
Dunbar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
